    </div>
  </nav>
</div>

<div id="about-modal" class="modal modal-fixed-footer">
  <div class="modal-content">

    <h5>About "MetroFuture in Action"</h5>
    <p>
      This site highlights the work of the Metropolitan Area Planning Council (MAPC), the regional planning agency for
      the 101 cities and towns of Greater Boston. Our long-term regional plan, MetroFuture, guides our work, and the
      projects shown here demonstrate how we implement MetroFuture on the ground.
    </p>
    <p>
      You can use the map on the main page or the pull-down in the header bar to filter projects by municipality (that
      is, city or town), and by subregion (the "chapters" or groups of municipalities that comprise MAPC). Select a
      single project to view more details about that project.
    </p>
    <br />

    <h5>More About MAPC</h5>
    <p>
      The <a href="http://mapc.org" target="_blank">Metropolitan Area Planning Council</a> (MAPC) is the regional
      planning agency for the 101 cities and towns of Greater Boston. We work to improve Metro Boston’s livability – its
      prosperity, safety, health, climate resilience, equity, and distinctive character.
    </p>
    <p>
      We provide superb, easy-to-access planning services; we offer programs to save taxpayer money through group
      purchasing; and we serve as a regional "think tank", generating actionable data and analysis, advocating for
      regional priorities, and promoting best practices and collaboration.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="mailto:inquiries@mapc.org">
        Contact us
      </a>
      to learn how MAPC can help your community.
    </p>
    <br />

    <h5>More About MetroFuture</h5>
    <p>
      MetroFuture is MAPC's 30-year plan for the Greater Boston region. The plan guides all of MAPC's work.
    </p>
    <p>
      The MetroFuture plan supports smart growth and regional collaboration through the promotion of:
      <ul>
        <li>&bull; efficient transportation systems</li>
        <li>&bull; conservation of land and natural resources</li>
        <li>&bull; improvement of the health and education of residents</li>
        <li>&bull; an increase in equitable economic development opportunities for prosperity</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
    <p>
      Learn more about MetroFuture at <a href="http://metrofuture.org" target="_blank">metrofuture.org</a>.
    </p>
    <br /><br /><br /><br />

  </div>
